&gt; Kent,
&gt; 
&gt;   How owerriding runtest() better then overriding getName() method?
&gt;   I usually use something like this (probably already posted 
&gt; this to the 
&gt; list about 4 times):
&gt; 
&gt;   public class MyTest extends TestCase {
&gt;     int param;
&gt; 
&gt;     public MyTest(int param) {
&gt;        super(&quot;testParam&quot;);
&gt;        this.param = param;
&gt;     }
&gt;  
&gt;    public void testParam() {
&gt;      ... assert
&gt;    }
&gt; 
&gt;   public String getName() {
&gt;     return super.getName()+&quot; &quot;+param;
&gt;   }
&gt; 
&gt;   public static Test suite() {
&gt;     TestSuite s = new TestSuite(&quot;MyTest&quot;);
&gt;     s.addTest(new MyTest(10));
&gt;     s.addTest(new MyTest(11));
&gt;     s.addTest(new MyTest(12));
&gt;     return s;
&gt;   }
&gt; 
&gt; }
&gt; 
&gt;   regards,
&gt;   Eugene
&gt; 
